The stay-at-home orders are government overreach, the conservative Ohio state Senate candidate says, and the labeling of some workers as “essential” arbitrary.
The Ohio protest was among a growing number staged outside governors’ mansions and state Capitols across the country.
The signs of frustration come as Trump has pushed for easing stay-at-home orders and tried to look ahead to restarting the economy.
“They seem to be protesters that like me and respect this opinion, and my opinion’s the same as just about all of the governors.
A Columbus Dispatch photo of Ackison and other protesters yelling through glass doors of the statehouse rocketed around the internet.